with step by step photo and video recipe whenever it is indo chinese or
street food manchurian recipes are always most requested one basically the
recipe is made with deep fried vegetable fritters stir fried in a flavoured
manchurian sauce within the manchurian spectrum dry gobi manchurian recipe
is most popular and sought after recipe
i have always been a huge fan of gobi manchurian recipe and it is perhaps
one of the frequent recipes i prepare at home as matter of fact manchurian
recipe is an all time favourite recipe in my entire family i personally like
the dry variation as a starter and the gravy version as a side dish to fried
rice or noodles recipe in this recipe i have tried to prepare a crisp
version of dry gobi manchurian which is generally prepared by street
vendors especially those sold and served in fair and barrow i do not like
the one which is served in the fine dining restaurant which is soft and soggy
the main trick is to add corn flour with plain flour which turns the gobi
fritters crisp and helps to hold the shape

furthermore some easy and important tips and suggestions while preparing the
dry gobi manchurian recipe firstly clean the gobi florets properly and
boil them in hot water for 2 minutes approximately this not only cleans and
kills all the unnecessary microorganisms but also cooks it evenly for the gobi
fritters secondly you can prepare the gobi fritters in advance and saute
with the manchurian sauce when it is required to maintain the crispiness you
can preserve it in a preheated oven lastly once the manchurian is prepared
it has to be served immediately as it may turn soggy if kept for a while

firstly in a large kadai heat 4 tsp oil and saute 2 clove garlic 1 inch ginger and 1 green chilli on high flame
also saute onion and 2 tbsp spring onion on high flame
further add capsicum and continue to saute till they slightly change colour
additionally add 2 tbsp tomato sauce 1 tsp chilli sauce 2 tsp vinegar 2 tsp soy sauce tsp pepper and tsp salt
mix well and saute for a minute
give a good mix until the gravy slightly thickens and turns translucent
mix gently making sure the sauce has coated well uniformly
finally transfer gobi manchurian to a serving bowl and garnish with chopped spring onions green serve with fried rice
